16:33.827 --> 16:35.760
<i> She was afraid</i>
<i> to say something.</i>

16:40.066 --> 16:41.899
<i> None of them have</i>
<i> to be afraid anymore.</i>

16:41.935 --> 16:43.301
[laughs]

16:43.336 --> 16:45.970
-[violet laughs]
-[hollywood] here, baby.

16:48.441 --> 16:49.674
How you doing?

16:50.343 --> 16:51.275
[hollywood laughs]

16:51.311 --> 16:53.978
[violet] hello, how are you?

16:54.014 --> 16:57.648
-[cooing]
-<i> ♪ I know it's hard</i>
<i> to turn ♪</i>

16:57.684 --> 16:59.517
oh, what is this, joaquin?

17:00.453 --> 17:02.453
It's a twist
on your blackberry pie.

17:03.323 --> 17:05.089
I added something
to give it a kick.

17:08.328 --> 17:10.461
I told you before.

17:10.497 --> 17:12.897
Don't be messing
with my recipes.

17:12.932 --> 17:18.069
Now I just hired you
back here, I know
you want to be a chef,

17:18.104 --> 17:20.104
but don't think
I won't pick you
out of the kitchen.

17:29.049 --> 17:30.348
Joaquin.

17:30.383 --> 17:31.382
[baby cooing]

17:34.654 --> 17:35.853
this is delightful.

17:37.190 --> 17:38.089
Really?

17:38.124 --> 17:39.657
[hollywood] it is really good.

17:39.692 --> 17:40.825
[both laughing]

17:44.798 --> 17:48.299
I think you might
have something here.
You tell your mama thank you.

17:48.334 --> 17:50.368
And tell her we'd love
to see her more.

17:50.403 --> 17:52.070
I'll let her know.

17:53.673 --> 17:55.473
You really like it?

17:55.508 --> 17:58.409
Yes, now go on
'cause I'm not
paying you to cook.

17:59.312 --> 18:00.311
Yet.

18:01.714 --> 18:02.680
[violet chuckles]

18:07.687 --> 18:08.753
mmm-hmm.

18:09.823 --> 18:13.224
Look who's warming up
to joaquin being back here.

18:13.259 --> 18:14.926
I still got my eye
on that boy.

18:16.062 --> 18:17.895
But this pie is great.

18:17.931 --> 18:19.831
-It's delicious.
-Mmm-hmm.

18:25.071 --> 18:26.304
That's for the whole year.

18:26.339 --> 18:27.205
-Yep.
-Mmm.

18:27.740 --> 18:28.673
Keke.

18:30.710 --> 18:32.410
[both laughing]

18:32.445 --> 18:34.545
micah west.

18:34.581 --> 18:36.414
-[laughs] hi.
-It's been forever.

18:37.617 --> 18:38.649
How you been?

18:38.685 --> 18:40.651
I'm good.

18:40.687 --> 18:43.688
I'm actually here
to take a class with
this photographer activist.

18:43.723 --> 18:45.156
Dude's like the next
gordon parks.

18:45.191 --> 18:46.390
Rahad stephens?

18:46.426 --> 18:48.693
-Oh, you know his work?
-I do.

18:48.728 --> 18:51.295
-I'm his ta.
Amongst other things.
-Ooh.

18:52.432 --> 18:53.664
Amongst other things.

18:53.700 --> 18:56.367
-Okay.
-Not like that.

18:56.402 --> 18:58.336
I run his nft accounts.

18:58.371 --> 19:00.204
He has an aversion
to the internet.

19:00.240 --> 19:01.539
It takes away from his art.

19:02.876 --> 19:04.442
You better get in there.

19:04.477 --> 19:05.676
-Yeah.
-[laughs]

19:05.712 --> 19:07.578
-he hates it
when his students are late.
-Yeah.

19:10.116 --> 19:11.916
Hey, it's good to see you.

19:11.951 --> 19:13.251
You too.

19:19.759 --> 19:20.925
Y'all did it, bro.

19:22.428 --> 19:24.128
-Um, excuse me.
-Yes, ma'am.

19:24.164 --> 19:26.430
I'm interested
in a csa subscription.

19:26.466 --> 19:27.865
Yes, absolutely.

19:27.901 --> 19:30.201
All right, it's farm
fresh produce delivered
straight to your door.

19:30.236 --> 19:31.869
Locally grown
by black farmers.

19:31.905 --> 19:35.072
We'll give you a quick tour
and we'll get you situated.
Okay?

19:35.108 --> 19:36.874
[ralph] mo'll be here
in a minute.

19:36.910 --> 19:38.809
-You got that final sale
count for me?
-Mo evans?

19:39.479 --> 19:40.745
The mo evans?

19:40.780 --> 19:43.080
You sent all of us a link
to her ted talk

19:43.116 --> 19:44.482
-about a hundred times.
-[laughing]

19:44.517 --> 19:46.584
I just wanna make sure
y'all familiar with her
when she get here.

19:47.320 --> 19:48.920
-All right?
-Yeah.

19:48.955 --> 19:49.820
[ralph] all right.

19:49.856 --> 19:50.955
[all laughing]

19:52.759 --> 19:56.494
so what are your intentions
with my friend sandy?

19:56.529 --> 19:57.662
It's been six months.

19:57.697 --> 20:00.665
None of us are getting
any younger.

20:00.700 --> 20:03.968
You need to do something
or let her find someone
who will.

20:05.638 --> 20:07.805
I'm gonna get
that coffee refill.

20:09.542 --> 20:11.175
Okay.

20:11.211 --> 20:13.878
Excuse me, parthena,
can I talk to you
for a minute?

20:15.114 --> 20:17.682
So I looked
over your books
like you asked.

20:18.651 --> 20:21.352
And the third account
is overdrawn.

20:22.555 --> 20:25.156
I know, still waiting
for debt relief money.

20:25.191 --> 20:29.860
Okay, I'm a little bit worried
about you falling so far
behind on your mortgage.

20:30.964 --> 20:32.964
You're almost 90 days
past due.

20:32.999 --> 20:35.533
I can't pay the bills
if the money's not there.

20:35.568 --> 20:38.135
Have you filed
for an extension
on your mortgage payment?

20:38.171 --> 20:39.036
Sure did.

20:39.072 --> 20:40.771
Three months ago.

20:40.807 --> 20:43.140
I'm still waiting
for the approval.

20:43.176 --> 20:45.176
It always comes
at the last minute.

20:45.211 --> 20:46.310
Yeah.

20:48.181 --> 20:49.347
We should go check on it.

20:49.382 --> 20:50.982
-I'll drive you.
-All right.

20:51.017 --> 20:52.016
Okay.

20:59.726 --> 21:00.725
[sighs]

21:07.767 --> 21:10.167
[darla] this isn't the end.
You begin again.

21:10.770 --> 21:12.036
Like you did before...

21:13.439 --> 21:14.605
...And they did before us.

21:17.076 --> 21:18.075
[car pulling up]

21:19.345 --> 21:20.344
oh, this is it.

21:20.947 --> 21:22.046
She's here, y'all.

21:23.216 --> 21:24.515
She's here. Come on.

21:24.550 --> 21:26.751
So is mo short for something?

21:26.786 --> 21:28.686
No, my brothers just
started calling me mo

21:28.721 --> 21:30.288
when I was little
and it stuck.

21:31.224 --> 21:33.491
My first word, I always
wanted mo.

21:33.526 --> 21:34.725
[darla laughs]

21:34.761 --> 21:37.595
[laughs] well, ain't nothing
wrong with wanting mo.

21:37.630 --> 21:38.896
Well, that's what
I tell the ladies.

21:38.931 --> 21:40.064
[all laughing]

21:41.134 --> 21:42.733
no, seriously,
thank you for coming, mo.

21:42.769 --> 21:44.669
-Mmm.
-You know, I've read
all your books

21:44.704 --> 21:48.406
and took your classes
and the seminar
about land trust.

21:48.441 --> 21:51.008
You know, I even sent
all the farmers your ted talk.

21:51.044 --> 21:52.176
Several times.

21:52.211 --> 21:53.844
Yep, with commentary.

21:53.880 --> 21:56.113
-[laughs]
-I first heard
about your name

21:56.149 --> 21:58.082
when I read up
on the freedom
georgia initiative.

21:58.117 --> 22:00.117
Well, it's inspiring
what they're doing.

22:00.153 --> 22:02.019
They're reclaiming the land.

22:02.055 --> 22:04.588
Black wall street
and a self-sustaining farm?

22:04.624 --> 22:05.856
-It's incredible.
-Yeah.

22:05.892 --> 22:08.426
We basically modeled our co-op
after yours.

22:08.461 --> 22:12.196
You know, csa set up.
Land trust next.

22:12.231 --> 22:13.898
You a real inspiration
around here.

22:14.967 --> 22:17.001
And this is my big sis, nova.

22:18.004 --> 22:19.937
She's writing an article
on the co-op.

22:20.606 --> 22:21.839
Nova bordelon.

22:22.508 --> 22:24.075
You have quite a reputation.

22:24.110 --> 22:25.509
All good, I hope.

22:26.279 --> 22:28.145
I don't shy away
from bad either.

22:29.482 --> 22:31.615
I've been watching
your profiles online.

22:32.085 --> 22:33.184
Powerful.

22:33.219 --> 22:35.453
Thank you, that land
means everything
to our family

22:35.488 --> 22:39.156
and my brother
sacrificed it all in order
to make this co-op work.

22:39.192 --> 22:42.159
Nothing extraordinary happens
without taking chances.

22:44.163 --> 22:46.597
[ralph] speaking of chances,
mr. Prosper been taking
a chance

22:46.632 --> 22:48.666
on this new youth program
we've been developing.

22:48.701 --> 22:49.900
-You wanna, um...
-Yes.

22:49.936 --> 22:52.503
-Yeah, beautiful, beautiful.
-[mo] let's do it. All right.

22:52.538 --> 22:54.305
-Hope to see you later, nova.
-You too.

22:57.009 --> 22:58.042
Excuse me.

22:59.178 --> 23:00.177
What you doing?

23:00.713 --> 23:02.513
-What?
-What?

23:02.548 --> 23:05.816
I saw the way y'all was
gazing and all that.

23:05.852 --> 23:07.485
Don't go pulling a nova, nova.

23:07.520 --> 23:09.687
-I know how you move.
-Don't.

23:09.722 --> 23:10.955
-I'm serious.
-Okay.

23:12.959 --> 23:13.958
[ralph] it's looking good.

23:19.699 --> 23:21.866
Y'all settle down, please.

23:21.901 --> 23:23.100
[indistinct conversations]

23:24.203 --> 23:25.903
look, I know it ain't much,
but please.

23:25.938 --> 23:27.671
[woman 1] ridiculous.
What am I supposed
to do with that?

23:27.707 --> 23:30.908
First you sit through
a million meetings,
what for?

23:30.943 --> 23:33.611
Once we cover overhead costs,
we'll be right back
where we were.

23:33.646 --> 23:35.579
When is that gonna be?
We all got bills to pay.

23:36.382 --> 23:37.548
Well, maybe a few weeks.

23:37.583 --> 23:38.749
-[parthena] maybe a few weeks?
-[woman 2] come on, ralph!

23:39.585 --> 23:41.752
One, two weeks.

23:41.788 --> 23:43.087
[group exclaiming]

23:43.122 --> 23:44.388
[indistinct speaking]

23:46.325 --> 23:49.260
like I said before,
this ain't nothing
but a pipe dream.

23:51.063 --> 23:52.062
Hey, hey!

23:54.434 --> 23:57.468
For those of you
I haven't met yet,
I'm mo evans.

23:57.503 --> 24:00.404
I'm here representing
the southern louisiana
federation of co-ops.

24:01.607 --> 24:03.641
What ralph angel and y'all
have accomplished

24:03.676 --> 24:06.544
over these last six months
is extraordinary.

24:06.579 --> 24:09.213
Eighty percent of those
doing the farming
are black and brown,

24:09.248 --> 24:11.482
but only 3% are owners.

24:11.517 --> 24:13.117
Well, it don't feel
any different.

24:13.152 --> 24:14.185
Well, it should.

24:15.588 --> 24:19.089
You are building
the foundation.
That is the hardest part.

24:19.125 --> 24:20.825
Okay, next is the house,
but you won't get there

24:20.860 --> 24:23.594
if you start measuring
the value of what you're doing
here to those checks.

24:27.600 --> 24:30.367
Every force out there
will try to tear you apart.

24:34.707 --> 24:35.673
Don't let 'em.

24:40.546 --> 24:43.314
I came to let you know
we've approved
your application to join us.

24:43.349 --> 24:44.215
[indistinct conversation]

24:45.618 --> 24:47.718
welcome to the 3%.

24:49.021 --> 24:50.087
[mouthing] thank you.

24:50.122 --> 24:51.121
[indistinct conversations]

24:54.227 --> 24:56.427
our revolution
is based on land.

24:56.462 --> 24:57.761
Know who said that?

24:57.797 --> 24:58.996
No.

24:59.999 --> 25:01.198
Malcolm.

25:01.234 --> 25:06.003
All the farmers that came
before us and died
on our land,

25:06.038 --> 25:07.238
they disrupted the system.

25:08.674 --> 25:10.241
They didn't just take
what was given to them,

25:11.010 --> 25:12.042
they demanded respect.

25:13.379 --> 25:14.378
This co-op...

25:16.749 --> 25:17.848
...Is for them.

25:18.885 --> 25:20.751
And now, it's our turn...

25:21.554 --> 25:22.887
...To disrupt the system.

25:22.922 --> 25:24.588
Reclaim what we lost.

25:25.191 --> 25:26.190
But...

25:27.493 --> 25:29.026
...The only way we could do it

25:29.695 --> 25:31.729
is if we move together...

25:33.099 --> 25:34.431
...As a unit.

25:35.868 --> 25:38.302
-[indistinct conversation]
-[man 1] makes sense.

25:38.337 --> 25:40.104
-[clapping]
-[woman 3] yeah,
let's stick together.

26:01.727 --> 26:02.760
[kenny] hey, billie.

26:03.629 --> 26:05.029
Thanks again.

26:05.064 --> 26:06.864
All that lida stuff
really gives me a headache.

26:06.899 --> 26:08.399
No, it's no problem.

26:08.434 --> 26:10.901
You get used to it,
it's like learning
another language.

26:11.437 --> 26:13.837
I mean, uh...

26:13.873 --> 26:16.040
A few of us are having
a bonfire this weekend,

26:16.075 --> 26:18.275
if you're not busy 'cause

26:18.311 --> 26:20.244
-I think you should
come along.
-Um...

26:20.279 --> 26:26.383
